# Connect (LinkedIn-style Database Design):
Exercise from Week 2 of CS50's Introduction to Databases with SQL.

This project involved designing a relational database for a professional networking platform similar to LinkedIn.

The goal was to model users, schools, companies, and relationships between them using a normalized relational schema.

## The database supports:
- Users with personal credentials
- Schools and universities
- Companies
- Connections between users
- Educational history
- Employment history

## Files Included
- schema.sql
- test.sql

## Topics Practiced
- Database design from real-world specifications
- Entity relationships and normalization
- Primary and foreign keys
- Many-to-many relationships using junction tables
- Composite primary keys
- Relational schema design
- Data modeling for social networks

## Skills Developed
- Designing a full relational database from scratch
- Modeling multiple entity types and relationships
- Building junction tables for complex relationships
- Applying database normalization principles
- Using foreign keys to ensure data integrity
- Translating real-world systems into SQL schemas
- Testing database design with sample data and queries
